I also need to track when crossovers and crossunders occur relative to the box boundaries. If a crossunder happens below the support box bottom, that signals a break. Similarly, a crossover above the resistance box top indicates a break.

To determine valid retests, I check if enough bars have passed since the initial break. For support, the price must touch the box top while closing below the bottom. For resistance, it must touch the box bottom while closing above the top.

Then I evaluate whether the current bar meets retest conditions for both directions—checking if price interacts with the box boundaries in the expected way. If a retest is valid and the trade direction permits, I generate an entry signal with the appropriate timestamp and price data. else:
            box_active[1] = False
        rBreak = np.nan
    
    # Detect crossovers and crossunders
    if i > 0:
        prev_close = df['close'].iloc[i-1]
        curr_close = df['close'].iloc[i]
        
        if box_active[0] and prev_close >= sBot_box and curr_close < sBot_box:
            sBreak = True
        
        if box_active[1] and prev_close <= rTop_box and curr_close > rTop_box:
            rBreak = True
    
    # Calculate support and resistance conditions
    s1 = df['high'].iloc[i] >= sTop_box and df['close'].iloc[i] <= sBot_box
    s2 = df['high'].iloc[i] >= sTop_box and df['close'].iloc[i] >= sBot_box and df['close'].iloc[i] <= sTop_box
    s3 = df['high'].iloc[i] >= sBot_box and df['high'].iloc[i] <= sTop_box
    s4 = df['high'].iloc[i] >= sBot_box and df['high'].iloc[i] <= sTop_box and df['close'].iloc[i] < sBot_box
    
    r1 = df['low'].iloc[i] <= rBot_box and df['close'].iloc[i] >= rTop_box
    r2 = df['low'].iloc[i] <= rBot_box and df['close'].iloc[i] <= rTop_box and df['close'].iloc[i] >= rBot_box
    r3 = df['low'].iloc[i] <= rTop_box and df['low'].iloc[i] >= rBot_box
    r4 = df['low'].iloc[i] <= rTop_box and df['low'].iloc[i] >= rBot_box and df['close'].iloc[i] > rTop_box
    
    sRetValid = (s1 or s2 or s3 or s4) and not pd.isna(sBreak) and sBreak
    rRetValid = (r1 or r2 or r3 or r4) and not pd.isna(rBreak) and rBreak
    
    if sRetValid and tradeDirection != 'Short':
        trade_num += 1
        entries.append({
            'trade_num': trade_num,
            'direction': 'long',
            'entry_ts': int(df['time'].iloc[i]),
            'entry_time': datetime.fromtimestamp(df['time'].iloc[i] / 1000, tz=timezone.utc).isoformat(),
            'entry_price_guess': df['close'].iloc[i],
            'exit_ts': 0,
            'exit_time': '',
            'exit_price_guess': 0.0,
            'raw_price_a': df['close'].iloc[i],
            'raw_price_b': df['close'].iloc[i]
        })
    
    if rRetValid and tradeDirection != 'Long':
        trade_num += 1
        entries.append({
            'trade_num': trade_num,
            'direction': 'short',
            'entry_ts': int(df['time'].iloc[i]),
            'entry_time': datetime.fromtimestamp(df['time'].iloc[i] / 1000, tz=timezone.utc).isoformat(),
            'entry_price_guess': df['close'].iloc[i],
            'exit_ts': 0,
